@This Is Rosie!!! they do give off bad vibes, but the so called vibes are more quantifiable and actually observable even if not easy. For instance microexpressions, body language, movement patterns and so on. Smell can also contribute when you're right next to them, humans can smell anger, stress, fear, and maybe disgust. We are really bad at it compared to for instance dogs, but we can still do it. 

Bad vibes might for instance even be that they are behaving in a subtly contradictory way or in a way that implies bad things if they don't have any disabilities (for instance if you have nerve damage in your face making some facial muscles paralyzed, that will creep some people out unfortunately, but it won't be as unsettling as someone who can not do that but still does). Another thing that is very common to give bad vibes is when someone is laser focused on getting something specific from you that they know is not easily parted with. For instance getting money from you, or sex, or an item. If that person isn't really obvious about it, they will still have an unusual behavioural pattern.  

I am sorry if I have rambled on too much, this is just a fascinating topic to me. I am an autist (with ADHD) so a lot of things normal people instinctively subconsciously read from others I have to actively look for. I am very grateful I was lucky enough to unintentionally train myself from early childhood to read faces through watching a lot of acting, but real life is not as wonderfully standardized and stripped of irrelevant elements (to "the story") as formalized acting. 

Real people have all sorts of things going on in their life simultaneously, and for someone like me it can sometimes be difficult to know if a stranger at a party who is listening to a few of us talk and occasionally interjects  is moving from side to side too much and looking aside a lot because they are way too bored, or naturally restless and don't like eye contact (I don't like too much uninterrupted eye contact either, it feels so aggressive!), or if they need to go to the bathroom but keep putting it off because they want to finish up the conversation with all of us whether out of interest or social obligation. 
Plus I have to actively focus and look for these signs, I get so easily distracted by even random background noises that others don't notice.
